    <briefdescription>
<para>Type trait to decay a type (remove references, const, and volatile). </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Removes both reference qualifiers (lvalue and rvalue) and cv-qualifiers (const and volatile) from a type. This is similar to std::decay but without STL.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Type</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The type to process</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
@SINCE_2_5.16</para>
